        <updateDate>2016-03-18T20:35:06Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><strong>Encouraging Americans to Save Act </strong></p> <p>This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to expand the tax credit for retirement savings contributions to: (1) make such credit refundable; (2) allow individual taxpayers (excluding dependents and full-time students) who have attained age 18 as of the close of the taxable year a credit for 50% of their retirement savings contributions up to $1,000; (3) increase the maximum income threshold for determining eligibility for the credit; and (4) allow direct deposit of credit amounts into the taxpayer's retirement savings vehicle (e.g., MyRA or Roth IRA account). </p> <p>The Department of the Treasury shall educate taxpayers on the benefits of the credit for retirement savings contributions. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
